item.title: Can som1 help me with the tele's on the emote tab
item.dc:creator: @T-R-A-V-I-S T-R-A-V-I-S
item.description:
@T-R-A-V-I-S wrote:

ok ill tell you step by step

go to client.java
ctrl+f
customCommand(“home”); //made by Musicmad441

then you will see something like this

break; case 163: if(teleblock == true){ //Made by musicmad441 sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); } else { customCommand("home"); //made by Musicmad441 }

then change “home” to what you want it to be

then close out and go back into client.java

ctrl+f
home

then you will see

} else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("home")) { if(teleblock == true){ sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); //made by Musicmad441 } else { teleportToX = 3189; teleportToY = 9758; sendMessage("You teleport to Home."); } }

now change the cords and name
save compile and your done

item.title: Can som1 help me with the tele's on the emote tab
item.dc:creator: @Ic3_Barrage Ic3 Barrage
item.description:
@Ic3_Barrage wrote:

Go on to a client where when you right click something you see “, ####” after it.
The number after it is the Case for that tele. Search for its case. Like case 133: for example.
and make it look like this…
This is my case for barrows.

		case 162: // Barrows
		teleportToX = 3564;
		teleportToY = 3288;
			break;

Change the numbers in Red to your co-ords.
